/*!
\page bobui-android-generate-deployment-settings.html
\ingroup cmake-commands-bobuicore

\title bobui_android_generate_deployment_settings
\keyword bobui6_android_generate_deployment_settings

\summary {Generates the deployment settings file needed by androiddeploybobui.}

\include cmake-find-package-core.qdocinc

\cmakecommandsince 6.0
\warning This command is deprecated since BobUI 6.5. Use \l bobui_add_executable instead.
\cmakecommandandroidonly

\section1 Synopsis

\badcode
bobui_android_generate_deployment_settings(target)
\endcode

\versionlessCMakeCommandsNote bobui6_android_generate_deployment_settings()

\section1 Description

The \c{androiddeploybobui} tool expects a deployment settings file as input. This
command reads CMake variables and properties of the \c{target} to generate such
a file in the target's binary directory. Upon return, the full path to this file
is available in the target's \c{BOBUI_ANDROID_DEPLOYMENT_SETTINGS_FILE} property.

\section2 CMake Variables

A number of variables are used while generating the deployment settings file.
Some are provided by BobUI, others by CMake or the Android NDK.

\list
\li \l{cmake-variable-ANDROID_NDK_HOST_SYSTEM_NAME}{ANDROID_NDK_HOST_SYSTEM_NAME}
\li \l{cmake-variable-ANDROID_SDK_ROOT}{ANDROID_SDK_ROOT}
\li \c{CMAKE_ANDROID_ARCH_ABI}
\li \c{CMAKE_ANDROID_NDK}
\li \c{CMAKE_SYSROOT}
\li \l{cmake-variable-BOBUI_ANDROID_APPLICATION_ARGUMENTS}{BOBUI_ANDROID_APPLICATION_ARGUMENTS}
\li \l{cmake-variable-BOBUI_HOST_PATH}{BOBUI_HOST_PATH}
\endlist

\section2 Target Properties

The properties below will be read from the specified \c{target}. Note that this
command is called as part of target finalization (see
\l{bobui6_finalize_target}{bobui_finalize_target()}). If you are using
\l{bobui6_add_executable}{bobui_add_executable()} to create the target and you need to
modify some of these target properties, you need to ensure that target
finalization is deferred. See \l{bobui6_add_executable}{bobui_add_executable()} for
how to accomplish this.

\list
\li \l{cmake-target-property-BOBUI_ANDROID_DEPLOYMENT_DEPENDENCIES}{BOBUI_ANDROID_DEPLOYMENT_DEPENDENCIES}
\li \l{cmake-target-property-BOBUI_ANDROID_EXTRA_LIBS}{BOBUI_ANDROID_EXTRA_LIBS}
\li \l{cmake-target-property-BOBUI_ANDROID_EXTRA_PLUGINS}{BOBUI_ANDROID_EXTRA_PLUGINS}
\li \l{cmake-target-property-BOBUI_ANDROID_MIN_SDK_VERSION}{BOBUI_ANDROID_MIN_SDK_VERSION}
\li \l{cmake-target-property-BOBUI_ANDROID_PACKAGE_SOURCE_DIR}{BOBUI_ANDROID_PACKAGE_SOURCE_DIR}
\li \l{cmake-target-property-BOBUI_ANDROID_TARGET_SDK_VERSION}{BOBUI_ANDROID_TARGET_SDK_VERSION}
\li \l{cmake-target-property-BOBUI_ANDROID_COMPILE_SDK_VERSION}{BOBUI_ANDROID_COMPILE_SDK_VERSION}
\li \l{cmake-target-property-BOBUI_ANDROID_PACKAGE_NAME}{BOBUI_ANDROID_PACKAGE_NAME}
\li \l{cmake-target-property-BOBUI_ANDROID_APP_NAME}{BOBUI_ANDROID_APP_NAME}
\li \l{cmake-target-property-BOBUI_ANDROID_APP_ICON}{BOBUI_ANDROID_APP_ICON}
\li \l{cmake-target-property-BOBUI_ANDROID_VERSION_NAME}{BOBUI_ANDROID_VERSION_NAME}
\li \l{cmake-target-property-BOBUI_ANDROID_VERSION_CODE}{BOBUI_ANDROID_VERSION_CODE}
\li \l{cmake-target-property-BOBUI_ANDROID_LEGACY_PACKAGING}{BOBUI_ANDROID_LEGACY_PACKAGING}
\li \l{cmake-target-property-BOBUI_QML_IMPORT_PATH}{BOBUI_QML_IMPORT_PATH}
\li \l{cmake-target-property-BOBUI_QML_ROOT_PATH}{BOBUI_QML_ROOT_PATH}
\li \l{cmake-target-property-bobui_no_entrypoint}{bobui_no_entrypoint}
\endlist

Upon return, the \c{BOBUI_ANDROID_DEPLOYMENT_SETTINGS_FILE} target property will
contain the location of the generated deployment settings file.

\sa {bobui6_android_add_apk_target}{bobui_android_add_apk_target()},
    {bobui6_finalize_target}{bobui_finalize_target()}

\section1 Example

\snippet cmake-macros/examples.cmake bobui_android_deploy_basic
*/
